<main class="wrap">
  <section class="hero card">
    <h1>AA2 Hardlinker</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      A community-made tool for updating clothing textures in the game Artificial Academy 2. It checks what you already have,
      downloads only what changed, verifies file integrity, and refreshes symlinks so the game sees the latest textures.
    </p>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="btn primary" href="{{ site.links.downloadWindows }}">Download for Windows</a>
      <a class="btn" href="{{ site.links.downloadLinux }}">Download for Linux</a>
      <a class="btn ghost" href="{{ site.links.releases }}">All releases</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="preview card">
    <figure class="preview__frame">
      <img src="/assets/preview.png" alt="AA2 Hardlinker program preview">
      <figcaption>Live updater view</figcaption>
    </figure>
  </section>

  <section class="grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>What it does</h2>
      <p>
        It gives access to the latest community-made textures in a single click.<br>
        No more manual downloads, no more copying files around, no more wondering if you have the latest version. Just run the program and it takes care of everything for you.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2>Key features</h2>
      <ul class="features">
        <li>Step-by-step update flow with progress feedback</li>
        <li>Only downloads missing or changed files</li>
        <li>MD5 and size verification for integrity</li>
        <li>Parallel downloads for faster updates</li>
        <li>Cancelable runs with prerequisite checks</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="card install">
    <h2>Quick setup</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Download the latest archive for your OS.</li>
      <li>Extract it inside your AA2 install directory.</li>
      <li>Run the updater from the same folder as <strong>AA2Play.exe</strong>.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="card troubleshoot">
    <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
    <p>If the program fails to start on Linux, install the required webkit package:</p>
    <pre class="code"><code># Debian/Ubuntu
sudo apt install libwebkit2gtk-4.1-0

# Fedora
sudo dnf install webkit2gtk4.1

# Arch
sudo pacman -S webkit2gtk-4.1</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="card community">
    <h2>Community</h2>
    <p>This is a community effort. Contributions are welcome.</p>
    <p><a class="text-link" href="{{ site.links.repository }}">Contribute on GitHub</a></p>
  </section>
